name: structural-contours-of-the-hauterivian-qezeltash-formation-of-northern-afghanistan-qezeldpafg-s
notes: This shapefile contains polylines that describe structural contours (subsea elevation) of the Hauterivian Qezeltash formation in northern Afghanistan. Hauterivian sandstones are a reservoir rock of the Jurassic subsalt petroleum systems of the Afghan-Tajik and Amu Darya basins.
